{"id": "318", "post": "<div class=\"post-318 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-madgenius-com tag-openvz\" id=\"post-318\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/madgenius-64mb-xenopenvz-vps/\" rel=\"bookmark\">MadGenius \u2013 $6 64MB Xen/OpenVZ VPS</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/madgenius-com/\" rel=\"tag\">madgenius.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openvz/\" rel=\"tag\">openvz</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> August 14, 2009 @ 11:25 pm, by LowEndAdmin</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a href=\"http://www.madgenius.com/vps.html\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/images/madgenius.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"screenshot litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"/media/images/madgenius.jpg\" alt=\"MadGenius\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a> Via <a href=\"http://www.webhostingtalk.com/showthread.php?t=883042\">this WHT offer</a>. <a href=\"http://www.madgenius.com/\">Mad Genius</a> is now offering some <a href=\"http://www.madgenius.com/vps.html\">Xen or OpenVZ VPS plans</a> from <b>$6/month</b>. For their \u201cMad Host 1 64\u201d plan, you get:</p><ul><li>64MB memory</li><li>2.5GB storage</li><li>100GB/month data transfer</li></ul><p>I could not work out where the VPS is situated. From their home page it says they are Minneapolis based business. From traceroute to their web site it lands in New York via Frontier (with a very bad latency).</p><p>And as of the logo. Hmm \u2014 are you sure you really want to trust your virtual server with a \u201cmad scientist\u201d?! About page is empty, and the SSL certificate is not valid. Although the domain has been registered for the last 10+ years, and the same logo has been used before. However I would be wary hosting with a mad genius, no matter how much a genius he might be.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fmadgenius-64mb-xenopenvz-vps%2F&amp;t=MadGenius%20-%20%246%2064MB%20Xen%2FOpenVZ%20VPS\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=MadGenius%20-%20%246%2064MB%20Xen%2FOpenVZ%20VPS&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fmadgenius-64mb-xenopenvz-vps%2F&amp;via=LowEndNetwork\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-twitter dpsp-no-label\" title=\"Share on Twitter\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?url=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fmadgenius-64mb-xenopenvz-vps%2F&amp;title=MadGenius%20-%20%246%2064MB%20Xen%2FOpenVZ%20VPS&amp;mini=true\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-linkedin dpsp-no-label dpsp-last\" title=\"Share on LinkedIn\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper\"></span></a></li></ul><div class=\"dpsp-total-share-wrapper\"><span class=\"dpsp-icon-total-share\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-to